&lt;p&gt;The Terminal application can also be started via Lauchpad under the â€˜Otherâ€™ group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Steps for a complete removal of R on macOS:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Start the Terminal application. The terminal console prompt, where the commands will be entered, is depicted by a &lt;code&gt;%&lt;/code&gt; or a &lt;code&gt;$&lt;/code&gt; sign. Which sign is shown, depends whether your default shell is zsh (&lt;code&gt;%&lt;/code&gt; sign) or bash (&lt;code&gt;$&lt;/code&gt; sign).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To delete the R application copy (âŒ˜C) the following line, paste (âŒ˜V) it behind the terminal console prompt and press return (â†©) to execute. Provide the macOS password when asked (the typed password will not be visble!).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo rm -r /Applications/R.app
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol start=&#34;3&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To delete the whole framework running behind R copy (âŒ˜C) the following line, paste (âŒ˜V) it behind the console prompt in the terminal and press return (â†©) to execute. No password will be asked anymore, as long as you do not close the terminal application.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo rm -r /Library/Frameworks/R.framework
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol start=&#34;4&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To be able to re-install R the installation receipts need to be removed. This is done by copying (âŒ˜C) the following lines (including the *) one by one, pasting (âŒ˜V) them behind the prompt in the terminal and pressing return (â†©) to execute.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo rm -r /private/var/db/receipts/org.r-project.*
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo rm -r /private/var/db/receipts/org.R-project.*
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol start=&#34;5&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Delete R application support by copying (âŒ˜C) the following line, pasting (âŒ˜V) it behind the prompt in the terminal and pressing return (â†©) to execute.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo rm -r ~/Library/Application Support/R
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol start=&#34;6&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clean the cache of R by copying (âŒ˜C) the following line, pasting (âŒ˜V) it behind the prompt in the terminal and pressing return (â†©) to execute.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo rm -r ~/Library/Caches/org.R-project.org
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol start=&#34;7&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To remove R preferences copy (âŒ˜C) the following line, paste (âŒ˜V) it behind the prompt in the terminal and press return (â†©) to execute.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo rm ~/Library/Preferences/org.R-project.org.plist
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol start=&#34;8&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deletion of all previously installed user packages is achieved by copying (âŒ˜C) the following line, pasting (âŒ˜V) it behind the prompt in the terminal and pressing return (â†©) to execute. A notification will be given in case the folder does not exist.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo rm -r ~/Library/R
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol start=&#34;9&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Delete user created environment variables, used at startup of R, copy (âŒ˜C) the following line, paste (âŒ˜V) it behind the prompt in the terminal and press return (â†©) to execute. A notification will be given in case the file does not exist.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo rm  ~/.Renviron
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol start=&#34;10&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Finally delete the user folder with additional settings by copying (âŒ˜C) the following line, pasting (âŒ˜V) it behind the prompt in the terminal and pressing return (â†©) to execute. A notification will be given in case the folder does not exist.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo rm -r ~/.R
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;alert alert-note&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div&gt;
    Having performed all 10 steps given above, your mac will be ready for a new installation of R. Leave the terminal console open for now, you might need it later on.
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;download&#34;&gt;Download&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At the time this post was written, the latest release of R was version 3.6.3. It has been updated to the latest release version 4.3.1 of R (nicknamed: &amp;ldquo;Beagle Scouts&amp;rdquo;) for macOS Big Sur or higher.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For newer versions of R than 3.6.3 the steps described below are the same and still correct, but start with a newer version of the downloaded package file of R. The screenshots in this post have not been updated. Therefore, what you see during your installation can (and probably will) differ with respect to the version number shown in the screenshots.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;alert alert-warning&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;For macOS there are four downloads for R available on the &lt;a href=&#34;https://cloud.r-project.org/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;R-project website&lt;/a&gt;. To see which version of macOS is installed on your mac, click on
&lt;i class=&#34;fab fa-apple  pr-1 fa-fw&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt; in the menu bar and select â€˜About This Macâ€™.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NOTE&lt;/strong&gt;: If you are using a mac with the newest M1 or M2 processor, download the &lt;strong&gt;Apple Silicon arm64&lt;/strong&gt; build!&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Download R for your specific version of macOS using one of the following links:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For macOS El Capitan (10.11.x) up to and including macOS Mojave (10.14.x): &lt;a href=&#34;https://cloud.r-project.org/bin/macosx/R-3.6.3.nn.pkg&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;
  &lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-download  pr-1 fa-fw&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt; R 3.6.3 (ca. 77 MB,  &lt;em&gt;regular&lt;/em&gt; 64-bit)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For macOS High Sierra (10.13.x) up to and including macOS Catalina (10.15.x): &lt;a href=&#34;https://cloud.r-project.org/bin/macosx/base/R-4.2.3.pkg&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;
  &lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-download  pr-1 fa-fw&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt; R 4.2.3 (ca. 89 MB,  &lt;em&gt;regular&lt;/em&gt; 64-bit)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For macOS Big Sur (11.x) and higher (&lt;strong&gt;Intel 64-bit&lt;/strong&gt; build): &lt;a href=&#34;https://cloud.r-project.org/bin/macosx/big-sur-x86_64/base/R-4.3.1-x86_64.pkg&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;
  &lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-download  pr-1 fa-fw&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt; R 4.3.1  (ca. 92 MB, &lt;em&gt;notarized and signed&lt;/em&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Intel 64-bit&lt;/strong&gt; build)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For macOS Big Sur (11.x) and higher (&lt;strong&gt;Apple silicon arm64&lt;/strong&gt; build for M1 or M2 processor MACS only): &lt;a href=&#34;https://cloud.r-project.org/bin/macosx/big-sur-arm64/base/R-4.3.1-arm64.pkg&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;
  &lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-download  pr-1 fa-fw&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt; R 4.3.1  (ca. 90 MB, &lt;em&gt;notarized and signed&lt;/em&gt; &lt;strong&gt;ARM 64-bit&lt;/strong&gt; build)&lt;/a&gt; &lt;!--Due to an error in the release for the Apple silicon arm64 build, use the above download for the Intel 64-bit version!--&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;alert alert-note&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div&gt;
    macOS Ventura (13.x) users: there is a known bug in Ventura preventing installations from some locations without a prompt. If the installation fails, move the downloaded file away from the &lt;em&gt;Downloads&lt;/em&gt; folder (e.g., to your home or Desktop)
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;installation&#34;&gt;Installation&lt;/h2&gt;
