&lt;p&gt;The remedy for this issue is not difficult, just perform the following steps:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Go to the open terminal console. If you do not have one yet, open the Terminal application from Finder &amp;gt; Applications &amp;gt; Utilities (shorcut: â‡§âŒ˜U) or via Lauchpad under the â€˜Otherâ€™ group. The terminal console prompt, where the commands will be entered, is depicted by a &lt;code&gt;%&lt;/code&gt; or a &lt;code&gt;$&lt;/code&gt; sign. Which sign is shown, depends whether your default shell is zsh (&lt;code&gt;%&lt;/code&gt; sign) or bash (&lt;code&gt;$&lt;/code&gt; sign).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Copy (âŒ˜C) the following line, paste (âŒ˜V) it behind the prompt in the terminal console and press return (â†©) to execute the command.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;defaults write org.R-project.R force.LANG en_US.UTF-8
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol start=&#34;3&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quit the active terminal console by typing &lt;code&gt;exit&lt;/code&gt; and pressing return (â†©) to execute. To quit the Terminal application completely you can use the keyboard shortcut: âŒ˜Q or navigate the mouse pointer to the menu bar and click â€˜Terminalâ€™ &amp;gt; â€˜Quit Terminalâ€™.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Go back to the R Console and quit the R application either by:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Typing &lt;code&gt;q()&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;quit()&lt;/code&gt; behind the R Console prompt (indicated by the &lt;code&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; sign) and pressing return (â†©) to execute.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using the keyboard shortcut: âŒ˜Q&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Navigating the mouse pointer to the menu bar and clicking â€˜Râ€™ &amp;gt; â€˜Quit Râ€™&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Navigation the mouse pointer to the top left corner of the R Console window and clicking on the red ball&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;No matter what you choose, you will always be asked whether you want to save a workspace image as shown in &lt;a href=&#34;#figure-r_app_save_workspace2&#34;&gt;Figure 17&lt;/a&gt; below. Just click on the &lt;strong&gt;â€˜Don&amp;rsquo;t Saveâ€™&lt;/strong&gt; button to end the R application.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
















